    <thetext>Description of problem:
If user deletes let&apos;s say one raid member on sda, anaconda automatically deletes all members on other disks, without any notice

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
Fedora 26 Alpha / x86_64

How reproducible:
always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create RAID1 over two disks, finish installation, start new installation
2. IN blivet-gui delete one raid member

Actual results:
All raid members are deleted

Expected results:
Anaconda should inform user that all members will be deleted, via pop-up message or something appropriate

Additional info:</thetext>
